==Awards and recognition==
{{Main|List of awards and nominations received by Zendaya}}
[[File:Zendaya MTV Awards 2.jpg|thumb|Zendaya at the [[2018 MTV Movie & TV Awards]]|200x200px]]
In 2016, Zendaya was featured on [[Forbes]]' [[Forbes 30 Under 30|30 under 30]] list.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Zendaya |url=https://www.forbes.com/profile/zendaya/ |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230312055009/https://www.forbes.com/profile/zendaya/ |archive-date=March 12, 2023 |access-date=May 21, 2023 |website=Forbes |language=en}}</ref> She was included on ''[[Time (magazine)|TIME]]'' magazine's [[Time 100|annual list of the 100 most influential people in the world]] in 2022; ''Dune'' director Denis Villeneuve wrote of her saying, "She is an autonomous creative force herself. A cultural icon in the making. A person driven by pure inspiration, empathy, and respect for her craft, who uses authenticity as a new superpower [...] Zendaya is the future. And there is nothing more comforting to me. This is only the beginning".<ref>{{Cite magazine |date=May 23, 2022 |title=Zendaya: The 100 Most Influential People of 2022 |url=https://time.com/collection/100-most-influential-people-2022/6177806/zendaya/ |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220523200109/https://time.com/collection/100-most-influential-people-2022/6177806/zendaya/ |archive-date=May 23, 2022 |access-date=May 21, 2023 |magazine=Time |language=en}}</ref> In that same year, ''[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]'' ranked her on its list of the 500 most influential figures in global media.<ref>{{Cite web |last=viapiuser |date=December 22, 2020 |title=Zendaya |url=https://variety.com/exec/zendaya/ |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221229155326/https://variety.com/exec/zendaya/ |archive-date=December 29, 2022 |access-date=May 21, 2023 |website=Variety |language=en}}</ref>

In [[72nd Primetime Emmy Awards|2020]], at age 24, Zendaya became the youngest recipient of the [[Primetime Emmy Award for Outstanding Lead Actress in a Drama Series]], winning for her role as [[List of Euphoria characters#Ruby "Rue" Bennett|Rue Bennett]] in the [[HBO]] drama series ''[[Euphoria (American TV series)|Euphoria]]''. After winning the award again at the [[74th Primetime Emmy Awards|2022 Primetime Emmy Awards]], she became the youngest two-time acting winner.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Grobar |first=Matt |date=September 12, 2022 |title=Zendaya Again Sets Emmy Record With 'Euphoria' As Youngest Two-Time Acting Winner, Thanks "Anyone Who Has Loved A Rue, Or Feels Like A Rue" |url=https://deadline.com/2022/09/zendaya-wins-2022-emmy-lead-actress-drama-series-1235111829/ |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230307055311/https://deadline.com/2022/09/zendaya-wins-2022-emmy-lead-actress-drama-series-1235111829/ |archive-date=March 7, 2023 |access-date=February 24, 2023 |website=[[Deadline Hollywood]]}}</ref> Zendaya received the [[CinemaCon|CinemaCon Star of the Year Award]] in 2023.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Gardner |first=Chris |date=April 28, 2023 |title=Zendaya Recalls First Date at 15 to See 'Spider-Man' in 3D |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/movies/movie-news/zendaya-spider-man-date-tom-holland-1235405443/ |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230429021217/https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/movies/movie-news/zendaya-spider-man-date-tom-holland-1235405443/ |archive-date=April 29, 2023 |access-date=April 28, 2023 |website=The Hollywood Reporter |language=en-US}}</ref>

